Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing. Defendant to have no contact with Victim A/Witness A/Witness B/Witness C listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key. If the defendant has a passport he is to surrender his passport to the Waukesha Criminal Traffic Office (Room C226) within 24 hours of release from custody. Defendant is not permitted to apply for the issuance, duplicate nor renewal of a passport and/or passport card during the pendency of this action.
